Source: halos-browser-trust
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Matti Airas <matti.airas@hatlabs.fi>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://github.com/halos-org/halos-browser-trust
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: halos-browser-trust
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, libnss3, p11-kit-modules
Description: Make on-device browsers trust the system CA store
 So Chromium, Firefox and other NSS applications on a HaLOS desktop trust CAs
 installed via update-ca-certificates — notably the device's own auto-CA — with
 no manual per-user steps.
 .
 Chromium and other system-NSS apps: replaces libnss3's libnssckbi.so with a
 symlink to p11-kit-trust.so (re-asserted via a dpkg trigger so it survives
 libnss3 upgrades), exposing the system p11-kit trust store the way Fedora and
 Arch do by default but Debian omits.
 .
 Firefox bundles its own NSS and root store, so a Firefox enterprise policy at
 /etc/firefox/policies/policies.json installs the system CA file instead.
 .
 Pulled in by the halos-desktop metapackage, so it lands only on desktop
 variants.
